        "name": "Spider",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Other Giant Spiders",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 320",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 320",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 320,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "A staggering number of species of giant spider exist in the world. Some, like the dream spider, whose venom creates strange hallucinations, are relatively small. Others, like the lumbering giant ogre spider, are larger than horses.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "name": "Spider Allies",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 320",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 320",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 320,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Though they are vermin incapable of forming true alliances, spiders show up alongside many types of creatures, and sometimes even nest inside skeletons or other hollow undead creatures. Spellcasters sometimes call upon spiders using summon animal, and spider swarms have a way of popping up just about anywhere at the most inopportune times.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Monster Core pg. 320",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Monster Core pg. 320",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Monster Core",
            "page": 320,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Few everyday vermin inspire as much dread as the infamous spider.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
